<h1 class="pagetitle">Castle Age Optimizer 2.0: Introduction</h1>

<p>
  If you got here, you probably already know what <%= link_to "Castle Age", "http://apps.facebook.com/castle_age", :target => "_blank" %> is,
  but just in case... Castle Age is a MMORPG <%= link_to 'Facebook', "http://facebook.com", :target => "_blank" %> game in which you can
  battle other players, monsters and other nasty beasts gathering equipment along the way. I am not associated with Facebook or the makers
  of Castle Age.  I designed this software application to optimize my gameplay and decided to share it with others.  It does not play the
  game for you and it does not connect to the game through scripts or any other method to gather information or simulate gameplay.
</p>

<h1 class="block">How do I get started?</h1>

<p>
  <ul>
    <% unless user_signed_in? %>
      <li>
        Start by <%= link_to 'Signing Up', new_registration_path('user') %> for an account.
      </li>
      <br/>
    <% end %>
    <li>
      Create one or more profiles which represent your Castle Age profile energy, stamina, health, attack and defense,
			plus runes and item archive.
    <br/>
    <li>
      Next, you may enter generals, soldiers, lands, magic and blacksmith items manually.  I've designed a method for uploading specific
      files which can be downloaded from Castle Age (web3/web4) and subsequently uploaded into COPTER.  You can upload the files as often
 			as you like, easy-peasy-lemon-squeezy.  If you want to play pretend, you can alter all of your inventory to be the ultimate warrior
 			and then come back to reality by uploading your inventory and getting a real representation of your character.
    </li>
    <br/>
    <li>
      Next, look over your soldier list when invading or being invaded. Look over your weapon list. Check out your top attack and
      top defense items.  See what better items exist.  Find out what land to buy next to get the greatest return on your investment (ROI).
    </li>
    <br/>
    <li>
      Lastly, this is a work in progress, so if you see a bug, or think you see a bug, kill it by contacting me (email is in the
      footer). Also, if you have an idea, share it with me and I'll see if I can get it implemented.
    </li>
  </ul>
</p>

